System tables
Useful system tables:

Table	Purpose
system.databases	List of databases
system.tables	Tables and metadata
system.columns	Column names and types per table
system.parts	Storage/partition info


---
HTTP interface (curl)
ClickHouse exposes an HTTP API on port 8123:

# Port-forward if needed
oc port-forward -n agentic-aiops svc/clickhouse 8123:8123 &
# URL-encode your query
curl -s 'http://localhost:8123/?query=SELECT%20count()%20FROM%20otel.otel_logs'
curl -s 'http://localhost:8123/?query=SELECT%20count()%20FROM%20otel.otel_traces'
# Or POST the query body
curl -s -X POST 'http://localhost:8123/' -d "SELECT * FROM otel.otel_logs LIMIT 5 FORMAT TabSeparated"
2. Inside the cluster
From any pod in agentic-aiops:

oc exec -n agentic-aiops deploy/clickhouse -- wget -qO- 'http://127.0.0.1:8123/?query=SELECT%20count()%20FROM%20otel.otel_logs'
3. ClickHouse CLI
If the image includes clickhouse-client:

oc exec -it -n agentic-aiops deploy/clickhouse -- clickhouse-client --query "SELECT count() FROM otel.otel_logs"

4. From the agents / harness
Use the query_clickhouse tool from code/tools/agent_tools.py:

from code.tools.agent_tools import query_clickhouse
result = query_clickhouse("SELECT count() FROM otel.otel_logs FORMAT TabSeparated")
Or use the HTTP API directly (same as the tools):

import requests
r = requests.post("http://localhost:8123", data="SELECT count() FROM otel.otel_logs", timeout=30)
print(r.text)

5. Tables available
Table	Description
otel.otel_logs	Log records (Timestamp, ServiceName, Body, SeverityText)
otel.otel_traces	Spans (Timestamp, Duration, ServiceName, SpanName)
otel.otel_metrics	Metrics (or otel_metrics_gauge, otel_metrics_sum depending on exporter)
